pull_request.body:
fixes #13 

I updated the plugin to support webpack 5. It seems like webpack 4 still works, but 2-3 stopped working. So i guess this would be a breaking change.

@x1B i also switched the repo to use yarn 2, including [yarn pnp](https://yarnpkg.com/features/pnp) and [zero installs](https://yarnpkg.com/features/zero-installs). It means you no longer need to run yarn install, and there's no more node modules directory. Instead, the cache directory (which is much smaller than the node_modules dir) is committed to the repo. If you don't like that, I'm happy to revert some or all of those changes. Just let me know. If we turn off zero installs, the cache directory will be git ignored, but we can keep yarn pnp. If we turn off pnp, then we'd also turn off zero installs and bring back a node modules dir. Or we can go back to yarn 1 and turn off all of the changes.

issue.body:
## Summary

I am using the d.ts rollup feature on a project that exports an array of objects that share a type, and one of the fields on those objects is a function. The rolled up d.ts uses the function as a value, rather than as a type, which is a type error.

## Repro steps

clone https://github.com/bdwain/api-extractor-type-issue and run `yarn install && yarn extract`

  **Expected result:** 

```ts
export declare function helper(param: string): boolean;

export declare const items: {
    foo: string;
    bar: string;
    auth: typeof helper;
}[];
```

  **Actual result:** 

```ts
export declare function helper(param: string): boolean;

export declare const items: {
    foo: string;
    bar: string;
    auth: helper; //not the missing typeof
}[];
```

## Details

Unsure of the cause or solution.

## Standard questions

Please answer these questions to help us investigate your issue more quickly:

| Question | Answer |
| -------- | -------- |
| `@microsoft/api-extractor` version? | 7.31.2 |
| Operating system? | Mac |
| API Extractor scenario? | d.ts rollup |
| Would you consider contributing a PR? | No |
| TypeScript compiler version? | 4.8.3 (but it used the bundled 4.7.4) |
| Node.js version (`node -v`)? | 14.18.1 |

